        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 19 at 4:36PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 435 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southeast of Monroe, or 4 miles southwest of Sturdivants,
moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sturdivants.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
